description.description_en: Perennial herbs; stems to 100 cm tall, procumbent or erect, suffrescent at base, densely farinose; branches ascending, angled.Leaves alternate or lower ones subopposite, ovate to trullate, 1-4 cm long, 7-18 mm wide, obtuse to mucronulate at apex, cuneate at base, entire.Plants monoecious; staminate inflorescence a terminal densely packed spike, ca. 1 cm long; tepals 5, obovate; stamens 5; pistillate inflorescences smaller spikes clustered into a panicle.Utricles sessile, fascicled, bracts compressed, trullate-rhombic, 6-9 mm long, more or less toothed at base, connate only at base.
